        Top 10 Singles of the year so far - week 25:
        1 (3) Weeknd - Save Your Tears 1392 (1318)

        2 (1) Tiesto - The Business 1391 (1366)

        3 (2) Kid Laroi - Without You 1339 (1327)

        4 (4) Riton/Nightcrawlers/Mufasa/Hypeman 1331 (1289)

        5 (5) Nathan Evans - Wellerman 1243 (1227)

        6 (7) Dua Lipa - Levitating 1188 (1133)

        7 (6) Olivia Rodrigo - Driver's License 1184 (1184)

        8 (8) ATB/Topic/A7S - Your Love (9PM) 1093 (1070)

        9 (11) Weeknd - Blinding Lights 1056 (1021)

        10 (9) Anne-Marie/KSI/DFA - Don't Play 1049 (1049)

        Weeknd has 2 climbers: Save Your Tears to #1 and last year's Blinding Lights reaching the top 10 of 2021 for the first time. He could well do the same on the weekly chart (hit #1) next week.

        2 hits are no longer in the top 75 adding to their totals (Driver's License and Don't Play), the former could well re-enter when Traitor's sales start to fall. 3 of the 4 singles to be on chart for all 25 weeks this are in the top 10 above (#2, #6 and #9). The only other single on chart all year so far is Joel Corry's Head & Heart at #16 of the year with 977 points.
